# Bus — {{PARENT_NAME}}

<!--
  The bus is the parent-level communication archive. Every message routed by `sync`
  gets a short entry here, regardless of which module sent it or who it was addressed to.
  This gives the parent session (and the user) a single scrollable product-wide feed
  of cross-module activity.

  Location: <parent>/shared/bus.md
  Companion: <parent>/shared/bus-routing.log (append-only one-line-per-event log)
  Full model: references/module-communication.md §bus-semantics
  Rotation:  references/module-communication.md §retention-and-rotation

  Rules:
    - Append-only. Never edit historical entries.
    - sync is the only writer. Module sessions do not touch bus.md directly.
    - Each entry is a one-paragraph summary, not the full body. Full bodies live in
      the receiving module's inbox and the sender's outbox-sent archive.
    - Rotated content collapses into a Summary Block at the top of the archive file.
-->

